{"id": "d620a63fb98fa9c7d6f45fbf3b1d04e66f7c64379a2f8dba834fd13d0051b4a2", "item_id": "a751d81226:0", "text": "Turning Red © Disney/Pixar"}
{"id": "aa4a21b7e73c9afd8d2f8e0fe5dc4d654f281a889d64b3b8ecffdb6470c826a3", "item_id": "a751d81226:1", "text": "Hair & Fur Presets"}
{"id": "15782d9fb413c2b1785c95e0bcf6cfd1b219b4fa71ddbc58aa5f9b90006ada43", "item_id": "a751d81226:2", "text": "RenderMan now ships with useful Hair and Fur presets, check them out in the Preset Browser."}
{"id": "13ff292ac3c9fcf2964886392306cdbe4fd66af985d5c87bbc4145581fcdde30", "item_id": "a751d81226:3", "text": "LamaHairChiang is a layer-able version of the Pixar Chiang hair shader used in production at Pixar."}
{"id": "32434ec0b70cdd745ecd4800a89ede35f06ede0c5557631c8f612ac900aa9347", "item_id": "a751d81226:4", "text": "It is based on the"}
{"id": "ecc83f96c04d37a15cf69e8e39f1a09bdad66430cfdec9fb639098b6889eab9c", "item_id": "a751d81226:5", "text": "research at Disney Animation Studios"}
{"id": "c6e06b36f8db491b5ceb42e28a9bf2891fe518d03b76b01da2ec74cd2ddb1e47", "item_id": "a751d81226:6", "text": "and features several improvements over"}
{"id": "ccf31fc48275c143b867da4b33a4ee3f6d4e505c6b15e85616384686e98b23fe", "item_id": "a751d81226:7", "text": "PxrMarschnerHair"}
{"id": "452a2622fe313630e4b3533aa3f44928ca647f3ac225fb523077c9027218962c", "item_id": "a751d81226:8", "text": ", including improved convergence, more realistic tube-like specular response, and remapped color that is more indicative of the color picked at varying roughness levels."}
{"id": "1b277ef03e02dd057e69881d84411363c55a678dac15af2f0107995f3c91745a", "item_id": "a751d81226:9", "text": "Tips and Tricks"}
{"id": "33356e4be8f251e8d6903086708606cf1f20da879cff457a320f8762c319761f", "item_id": "a751d81226:10", "text": "To use it in conjunction with"}
{"id": "92a4da46d1ad59caadc98bd9d442300c4b902fe97f71ff82d5e8affa8dccd63e", "item_id": "a751d81226:22", "text": "PxrHairColor"}
{"id": "1321623eb406aa7d4f3f3e350b13b7aecb4e1224fa9bf76893269b8988c6e0f0", "item_id": "a751d81226:12", "text": ", make sure to keep the"}
{"id": "02beb5a4a5bbf2e1a7bfa703fa1025fd64d2b3ee74221c6711359a850646ea48", "item_id": "a751d81226:25", "text": "R Specular Color"}
{"id": "65e9a1c034cb9cfb91634f3ec515ca6a72e8eb2c4bb87639e29be63c66cc37ff", "item_id": "a751d81226:14", "text": "attribute set to white, and simply drive the hair color via"}
{"id": "00aefd1136a63df1bc7538f12337560bc6f6c9796600e1904f0cb139855e7301", "item_id": "a751d81226:15", "text": "Color TT"}
{"id": "f24d6e7ecaa31e610a3adc8db4af4975fdda31f1cf0ed75f2a67a41d9fa622f4", "item_id": "a751d81226:17", "text": "If using"}
{"id": "4ca2e457e68f79729fdca0ec5ae061ce0387e3a4702f33e2c4a3cd7ed4e99a7c", "item_id": "a751d81226:19", "text": ", please disable"}
{"id": "c4ab11eed4ea2f4b55019f8351241761d10aef024141255574e7297fcb058bd9", "item_id": "a751d81226:20", "text": "Remap TT Color"}
{"id": "45c24a28fba275daf7a343a9547242f06ec8dbf9e8b377dcc888ac5b0f3dd208", "item_id": "a751d81226:21", "text": ", as"}
{"id": "da245518e96b537384dab3bc688a2347fea00cd53154f0377b3945751ed68deb", "item_id": "a751d81226:23", "text": "already remaps the incoming color."}
{"id": "db6e46a75587252fac5061533a152764ed8cb735d0470f4778b0cd1a4108fdd6", "item_id": "a751d81226:24", "text": "SPECULAR"}
{"id": "e77c957c878a80bb3355f07751274339f9db4405ce39dc84e86fdf0db7ae04eb", "item_id": "a751d81226:26", "text": "Specular color for R lobe. This represents the first bounce of a ray encountering a hair curve. This lobe"}
{"id": "2cece95af5c1b1f9206c44cd260ed844c5cf2a98b90f7deb8098c7f604500cff", "item_id": "a751d81226:27", "text": "color should usually be WHITE, the response is consistent with dielectric materials of a surface shader."}
{"id": "cd265c5bd1cccdd3b91127e870b55f0760c26bef0c1ee6f1e2d58b8d295b51d6", "item_id": "a751d81226:28", "text": "In special cases, one might be art directed to tint this lobe - Do so with care."}
{"id": "52ea2da5d6bd79d74e1f2e933e179886df58ccf14a08192d45ac0a6f7b1c6ff0", "item_id": "a751d81226:29", "text": "TT Specular Color"}
{"id": "4b8034896a0be1da75e8b221999d1b40ddb1912ac07957261461214fb20c7780", "item_id": "a751d81226:30", "text": "Specular color for TT lobe. Main albedo of the full Chiang component."}
{"id": "41b349b816dbbdde32d5ef634c50003a8057172252439dd3b20cd19593f4aece", "item_id": "a751d81226:31", "text": "The default at 0.4 corresponds loosely to middle grey, considering visibility and bounces in the hair volume."}
{"id": "5f3576d9abc138b311240f6dea4691c1dacd88ded97174efeebfe3a75df404a5", "item_id": "a751d81226:32", "text": "Remap TT"}
{"id": "d0ed70be360bfd1fcf4594afc6dc0db68d3777522210a0f16e4c7ade08896e44", "item_id": "a751d81226:33", "text": "Color Remap the transmitted color so the final fur color looks closer to the actual color."}
{"id": "e1d89cb27546ce49535f1f5d0c0ca862075ce6379cf3f7d314a2717baffbd3ba", "item_id": "a751d81226:34", "text": "Primary Roughness"}
{"id": "b2a23f631c22e7f9ee5ba2be9193cc6bfa99f13bff9e62465d5b632ef76ee2af", "item_id": "a751d81226:35", "text": "Longitudinal Roughness for R in degrees"}
{"id": "a10420eaa85d5e956d8509dd733560ebbad3f00d17bc513898e21e9a4be15124", "item_id": "a751d81226:36", "text": "Transmit Roughness"}
{"id": "2af3d9d3117f05dec6872bf8c6e4be01bae7707c8bf11698cda06301dc509c72", "item_id": "a751d81226:37", "text": "Longitudinal Roughness for TT in degrees"}
{"id": "3001148dd91c24adbce9bbb9d6b358b38342c9de21db8e014b0a23ab487ddd24", "item_id": "a751d81226:38", "text": "Secondary Roughness"}
{"id": "57165a17765ab2b94e55f0e060c870ce99511497bfbdb114488d1103c823d514", "item_id": "a751d81226:39", "text": "Longitudinal Roughness for TRT in degrees"}
{"id": "7be797093ab654cf96ac38a070596c55c2d6835008f3cbecfb400a5d402b57ad", "item_id": "a751d81226:41", "text": "Azimuthal Roughness"}
{"id": "22b2190e89ae368175f306a7ff3e2659a664d9891507d921eaeb40dc94aff408", "item_id": "a751d81226:42", "text": "Specular Offset"}
{"id": "e839dae322050d0c09d467c6c9b86538b3384f8db96481fb952fbf7c9ca53507", "item_id": "a751d81226:43", "text": "Cone offset in degrees."}
{"id": "eefc81e9d819ec30a4265a547ca18b1bddcca10961e9bc9c548b531975d6953e", "item_id": "a751d81226:44", "text": "Refractive Index"}
{"id": "8986e6d72d2d0d892ff6f15d41c8d2c9c4bb3caf98bad3959e9d13cada20753a", "item_id": "a751d81226:45", "text": "Index of refraction."}
{"id": "c4ecf7d6880b8fc43211dfc10cc2e192358eecdb1f8582f4d7315a0eb403a785", "item_id": "a751d81226:46", "text": "R Specular Gain"}
{"id": "b3d7e7839ed87e8f63be3b6da9e3e5a6a31ba2e6ef1ec2bf24f3394f674ba2fd", "item_id": "a751d81226:47", "text": "Gain for R lobe of hair specular. This is like a clearcoat where the specular"}
{"id": "2ebfb4d1c192fec74fde09ce74a696381154a01d26c2ea963bc435341eb2f66c", "item_id": "a751d81226:48", "text": "is fairly sharp and glossy and normally not colored."}
{"id": "eb59b348b450ca4c91d22bf283afd4ab86290965be3bd25d6a8d333f53d688b6", "item_id": "a751d81226:49", "text": "TT Specular Gain"}
{"id": "11334a88b762d092634a59261a603b387abf8b5f59516c6057544308e673fc74", "item_id": "a751d81226:50", "text": "Gain for TT lobe of hair specular. This is a transmission-type (refraction)"}
{"id": "5c72ed8332bc5db380e0ae386c01443e0410abbfbeddaa1c99b5a0f2fc909ce7", "item_id": "a751d81226:51", "text": "specular with some volume attenuation."}
{"id": "49c03e4973a234904f728758305c75c6ca554d6dbeee25600acbcd94bcdd11e3", "item_id": "a751d81226:52", "text": "TRT Specular Gain"}
{"id": "a692b35d9de53c42b34611daa3aeaa3adfac5d2ac3c7e962f1ffb830ce849501", "item_id": "a751d81226:53", "text": "Gain for TRT lobe of hair specular.  This is a rougher and colored specular."}
{"id": "16aebd93f027dc43585e19c2225daf767ca8d2211bf0b8a4897b07e5b61bcc9e", "item_id": "a751d81226:54", "text": "TRRT Specular Gain"}
{"id": "29654ef8c6badbcf7492fcb5d8c7528b20ae11b774d11b6c9c7e5891724dbf57", "item_id": "a751d81226:55", "text": "Gain for residual energy, also a specular energy."}
{"id": "1d65b2d34798faf371f04ec53ca5bf29f7858f504317df876092db1d9b74871f", "item_id": "a751d81226:56", "text": "GLOBALS"}
{"id": "6946fd2382957f0655d0fd423e1699825089519d5bf4903df891d5d5f327a146", "item_id": "a751d81226:58", "text": "Shadow Color"}
{"id": "573e3dce5985c8d927bc9e692ce966552ded3230cf3f58d38e365eb6667e7391", "item_id": "a751d81226:59", "text": "ADVANCED"}
{"id": "32bdfbedab7b04880a73d6fd2666b9880e43f8075ef2ed7968b1bd5c49180e43", "item_id": "a751d81226:60", "text": "Specular Mollification"}
{"id": "ab8f72ca657ec3c5bbba0b150d93f1781378690e03bc7bf1ec2c26198de8f4b6", "item_id": "a751d81226:61", "text": "Improves convergence but may modify the fur's look."}
{"id": "a95b91e7ca13701736b0ee1d9e1e42b3b024e01ee9ea0781c2fb7ff93becaa7d", "item_id": "a751d81226:62", "text": "R Specular Lobe Name"}
{"id": "e577322e89b7188e40d72752cdbef9a5d202a29f33797034e285ca6fba053a71", "item_id": "a751d81226:63", "text": "Defines the name that can be used in LPE AOVs for the specular R lobe."}
{"id": "b3678731583506b0620f57c8e9e4b6440dcc5bc672884f1053b0be328e525b0d", "item_id": "a751d81226:64", "text": "TT Specular Lobe Name"}
{"id": "ac62a6f420b977c0d90d113be4d0ae358bea67a661cd4ea1627fa36d7689ab35", "item_id": "a751d81226:65", "text": "Defines the name that can be used in LPE AOVs for the specular TT lobe."}
{"id": "cbe6485a29870bb8c73cf13461dc5896effd70908575c7e86b532913f4cb3a9e", "item_id": "a751d81226:66", "text": "TRT Specular Lobe Name"}
{"id": "43ca062c996635df56e57ed28e5782902a53e512a65126adf9b1e122b5d60b92", "item_id": "a751d81226:67", "text": "Defines the name that can be used in LPE AOVs for the specular TRT lobe."}
{"id": "6e16ecf10bf2517d4f4f7f83379d68d4cc1f7d5a514f37cdad2ae3662f627e4e", "item_id": "a751d81226:68", "text": "Diffuse Lobe Name"}
{"id": "c97674be0d1dc103eb3612e304ff416376fd715b9007e09d3f162262c7388ab3", "item_id": "a751d81226:69", "text": "Defines the name that can be used in LPE AOVs for the diffuse lobe."}
{"id": "07d8eb6678c99a1d6cf84e00fe48e236992ca330aef0d7352ffa75c3d8dcebb8", "item_id": "a751d81226:70", "text": "Matte"}
{"id": "e08152a28c854677da43b771b8b0e1ec0d335e055acebdc92d41459d4ed231f5", "item_id": "a751d81226:71", "text": "Defines the name that can be used by the matte system, to output the weight of this lobe in the final material as an AOV."}
